  "notes": "Paulistano (SГЈo Paulo city / SГЈo Paulo State urban variety). Reference variety of Barbosa & Albano (2004, JIPA). Inherits the pt-BR base unchanged: full /t,d/ -> [tНЎКғ,dНЎК’] before [i,ЙӘ]; strong onset /r/ -> [КҒ~x~h]; coda /R/ tap [Йҫ] preferred (NOT retroflex), drops word-finally in infinitives; coda /S/ stays alveolar [s,z] by voicing assimilation (NO chiado); coda /l/ -> [w]; post-stressed and word-final reduction [ЙӘ КҠ Йҗ]; /ЙІ/ frequently -> [jМғ]; word-initial pretonic /eN/ -> [Д©] (entГЈo -> [Д©ЛҲtЙҗМғwМғ]). Prestige standard of southeastern media alongside Carioca. The retroflex 'r caipira' described by Amaral (1920) В§6b belongs to the surrounding caipira interior (pt-BR-x-caipira), NOT to the SГЈo Paulo capital variety modelled here вҖ” coda /r/ is a plain tap [Йҫ].",
